title: Publicity campaign to promote mental health launched
content_text: More than 70 activities, including talks, workshops, exhibitions, recreational activities and visits, will be organised over the next three months to promote a healthy workplace for employers and employees. At an opening ceremony today (October 10), the Secretary for Health and Welfare, Dr E K Yeoh, launched the Mental Health Month, which is a publicity campaign co-organised by the Health and Welfare Bureau annually with the support of the Hospital Authority, various government departments and non-government

the support of the Hospital Authority, various government departments and non-government 
    bodies to promote public awareness on the importance of mental health.  With "Mental Health and Work" 
    as this year's theme, the campaign is aimed at enhancing the awareness of employers and 
    employees on mental health and understanding the ways to deal with stress. The theme is to 
    tie in with the World Mental Health Day and will extend over two years to allow a broader 
    examination of matters which affect employees at every level. The opening ceremony was followed by a

examination of matters which affect employees at every level. The opening ceremony was followed by a 
    symposium with guest speakers to examine mental health at the workplace and organizational 
    strategies for dealing with mental health problems. A series of five other symposia on 
    healthy lifestyle at workplace will be organised across the territory to get across the
